=================================
PROBLME:
String palindrome 29
=================================
Write a program to find whether the given string is a palindrome or not

Input Format:
-------------
Read a string

Constraints:
-----------
string

Output Format:
--------------
If the given string is a Palindrome display “Palindrome”, else display “Not a Palindrome”.
===============
Sample Input 0
==============
madam
===============
Sample Output 0
===============
Palindrome
===============
Sample Input 1
===============
java
================
Sample Output 1
================
Not a Palindrome

=====================
Submitted Code
Language: C
=====================
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    int i,n,j=0;
    char str1[50],str2[50];
    scanf("%s",str1);
    n=strlen(str1);
        for(i=n-1;i>=0;i--)
        {
            str2[j]=str1[i];
            j++;
        }
    str2[j]='\0';
    
    if(strcmp(str1,str2)==0)
    {
        printf("Palindrome");
    }
    else
    {
        printf("Not a Palindrome");
    }
    return 0;
}

